      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>How could you use <sup>1</sup>H NMR, <sup>13</sup>C NMR, and IR spectroscopy to help you distinguish between the following structures?</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbTRVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--1146d2abdd9fe821be160b29c2a6353a4217277f/OChem_13_EC_015.jpg\" alt=\"An illustration shows the structures of 3-Methyl-2-cyclohexenone and 3-Cyclopentenyl methyl ketone. 3-Methyl-2-cyclohexenone shows a cyclohexenone bonded to a methyl group. 3-Cyclopentenyl methyl ketone shows a cyclopentene bonded to a carbonyl group bonded to a methyl group.\">",
